        <h2>Explanation</h2>
        <p><strong>What happens in the buggy version?</strong> We have a shared state variable (<code>progress</code>) that multiple asynchronous tasks try to update using <code>setTimeout</code>. Each task increments the progress and updates the bar, but because the tasks run concurrently (based on the event loop's timing), they can interfere with each other. For example:</p>
        <ul>
