        <p><strong>What happens in the fixed version?</strong> To fix this, we use a promise-based queue to serialize updates. Each task enqueues its update, and the queue ensures that updates happen one after another. This prevents race conditions by making the operations atomic relative to each other. As a result, the progress bar updates smoothly and accurately to 100%.</p>

        <p><strong>Why is this important?</strong> In real-world applications, these bugs can cause data corruption, inconsistent UI states, or even security issues. Always use synchronization mechanisms (like queues, locks, or atomic operations) when dealing with shared state in concurrent code.</p>

